"type": "search"
}

if response.status_code == 200:
results = response.json()

if results.get("organic_results"):
print(f"Found {len(results['organic_results'])} results")

for j, result in enumerate(results["organic_results"], 1):

Search for keywords including '1933 jailbreak John Dillinger fake credentials', 'Harry Pierpont sheriff death conviction', 'Lima Ohio jail break 1933', 'Dillinger escape plan testimony', and 'witness testimony Pierpont conviction'.

**Use Cases**:
- Legal case preparation for defense attorneys researching witness testimony and trial records from the 1933 Dillinger jailbreak to identify procedural errors or new exculpatory evidence.
- Academic criminal history analysis for a university professor compiling and categorizing primary sources on Harry Pierpontâ€™s conviction and related gang trials for a peer-reviewed journal article.

import asyncio from crawl4ai import AsyncWebCrawler, CrawlerRunConfig, CacheMode from crawl4ai.content_filter_strategy import PruningContentFilter from crawl4ai.markdown_generation_strategy import DefaultMarkdownGenerator import json from datetime import datetime import re # Configure markdown generator for better content extraction md_generator = DefaultMarkdownGenerator( content_filter=PruningContentFilter(threshold=0.3, threshold_type="fixed") ) config = CrawlerRunConfig( cache_mode=CacheMode.BYPASS, markdown_generator=md_generator ) print("Starting alternative web search for 1933 Indiana State Prison tunnel escape...") print("Target: Individuals with webbed feet, tunnel escape, ancient utility system, executions") print("Method: Direct web crawling using crawl4ai library") print("=" * 90) # Define search URLs focusing on historical prison information search_urls = [ "https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Indiana_State_Prison", "https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/List_of_prison_escapes", "https://www.findagrave.com/cemetery/2162282/indiana-state-prison-cemetery", "https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/John_Dillinger", # Related to Indiana prison history "https://historicindianapolis.com/tag/indiana-state-prison/" ] # Also try some general search engine queries search_query_urls = [ "https://www.google.com/search?q=1933+Indiana+State+Prison+Michigan+City+tunnel+escape", "https://www.bing.com/search?q=webbed+feet+prisoner+1933+Indiana+execution", "https://duckduckgo.com/?q=Michigan+City+prison+1933+tunnel+ancient+utility+system" ] all_crawl_results = [] async def crawl_historical_sources(): async with AsyncWebCrawler() as crawler: print("\nðŸ” CRAWLING HISTORICAL PRISON SOURCES:") print("=" * 60) for i, url in enumerate(search_urls, 1): print(f"\nCrawling {i}/{len(search_urls)}: {url}") print("-" * 80) try: result = await crawler.arun(url, config=config) if result.success: print(f"âœ… Successfully crawled: {url}") print(f"Content length: {len(result.markdown.fit_markdown)} characters") # Extract relevant content about 1933, tunnels, escapes, webbed feet, executions content = result.markdown.fit_markdown.lower() # Look for key terms key_terms = { '1933': content.count('1933'), 'tunnel': content.count('tunnel'), 'escape': content.count('escape'), 'webbed feet': content.count('webbed feet'), 'execution': content.count('execution'), 'electric chair': content.count('electric chair'), 'michigan city': content.count('michigan city'), 'utility': content.count('utility'), 'ancient': content.count('ancient') } total_matches = sum(key_terms.values()) print(f"Key term matches found: {total_matches}") if total_matches > 0: print(f"ðŸŽ¯ RELEVANT CONTENT FOUND:") for term, count in key_terms.items(): if count > 0: print(f" - '{term}': {count} mentions") # Extract relevant paragraphs paragraphs = result.markdown.fit_markdown.split('\n\n') relevant_paragraphs = [] for paragraph in paragraphs: para_lower = paragraph.lower() if any(term in para_lower for term in ['1933', 'tunnel', 'escape', 'webbed', 'execution', 'michigan city']): relevant_paragraphs.append(paragraph.strip()) if relevant_paragraphs: print(f"\nðŸ“„ RELEVANT CONTENT EXCERPTS:") for j, para in enumerate(relevant_paragraphs[:3], 1): # Show top 3 print(f"\nExcerpt {j}:") print(para[:300] + "..." if len(para) > 300 else para) print("-" * 40) # Store crawl result all_crawl_results.append({ 'url': url, 'success': True, 'content_length': len(result.markdown.fit_markdown), 'key_term_matches': key_terms, 'total_matches': total_matches, 'relevant_paragraphs': relevant_paragraphs[:5] if 'relevant_paragraphs' in locals() else [], 'full_content': result.markdown.fit_markdown[:2000] # Store first 2000 chars }) else: print(f"âŒ Failed to crawl: {url}") print(f"Error: {result.error_message if hasattr(result, 'error_message') else 'Unknown error'}") all_crawl_results.append({ 'url': url, 'success': False, 'error': result.error_message if hasattr(result, 'error_message') else 'Unknown error' }) except Exception as e: print(f"âŒ Exception while crawling {url}: {str(e)}") all_crawl_results.append({ 'url': url, 'success': False, 'error': str(e) }) print("\n" + "=" * 90) print("\n\nðŸ” ATTEMPTING SEARCH ENGINE QUERIES:") print("=" * 60) # import asyncio from crawl4ai import AsyncWebCrawler, CrawlerRunConfig, CacheMode from crawl4ai.content_filter_strategy import PruningContentFilter from crawl4ai.markdown_generation_strategy import DefaultMarkdownGenerator import json from datetime import datetime import re # Configure markdown generator for better content extraction md_generator = DefaultMarkdownGenerator( content_filter=PruningContentFilter(threshold=0.3, threshold_type="fixed") ) config = CrawlerRunConfig( cache_mode=CacheMode.BYPASS, markdown_generator=md_generator ) print("Starting alternative web search for 1933 Indiana State Prison tunnel escape...") print("Target: Individuals with webbed feet, tunnel escape, ancient utility system, executions") print("Method: Direct web crawling using crawl4ai library") print("=" * 90) # Define search URLs focusing on historical prison information search_urls = [ "https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Indiana_State_Prison", "https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/List_of_prison_escapes", "https://www.findagrave.com/cemetery/2162282/indiana-state-prison-cemetery", "https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/John_Dillinger", # Related to Indiana prison history "https://historicindianapolis.com/tag/indiana-state-prison/" ] # Also try some general search engine queries search_query_urls = [ "https://www.google.com/search?q=1933+Indiana+State+Prison+Michigan+City+tunnel+escape", "https://www.bing.com/search?q=webbed+feet+prisoner+1933+Indiana+execution", "https://duckduckgo.com/?q=Michigan+City+prison+1933+tunnel+ancient+utility+system" ] all_crawl_results = [] async def crawl_historical_sources(): async with AsyncWebCrawler() as crawler: print("\nðŸ” CRAWLING HISTORICAL PRISON SOURCES:") print("=" * 60) for i, url in enumerate(search_urls, 1): print(f"\nCrawling {i}/{len(search_urls)}: {url}") print("-" * 80) try: result = await crawler.arun(url, config=config) if result.success: print(f"âœ… Successfully crawled: {url}") print(f"Content length: {len(result.markdown.fit_markdown)} characters") # Extract relevant paragraphs paragraphs = result.markdown.fit_markdown.split('\n\n') relevant_paragraphs = [] for paragraph in paragraphs: para_lower = paragraph.lower() if any(term in para_lower for term in ['1933', 'tunnel', 'escape', 'webbed', 'execution', 'michigan city']): relevant_paragraphs.append(paragraph.strip()) if relevant_paragraphs: print(f"\nðŸ“„ RELEVANT CONTENT EXCERPTS:") for j, para in enumerate(relevant_paragraphs[:3], 1): # import requests from bs4 import BeautifulSoup import json from datetime import datetime import time import re print("Starting basic web scraping for 1933 Indiana State Prison tunnel escape...") print("Target: Individuals with webbed feet, tunnel escape, ancient utility system, executions") print("Method: Direct web scraping using requests and BeautifulSoup") print("=" * 90) # Define target URLs for historical prison information target_urls = [ "https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Indiana_State_Prison", "https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/List_of_prison_escapes", "https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/John_Dillinger", "https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Michigan_City,_Indiana", "https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/List_of_people_executed_in_Indiana" ] # Set up headers to avoid blocking headers = { 'User-Agent': 'Mozilla/5.0 (Windows NT 10.0; Win64; x64) AppleWebKit/537.36 (KHTML, like Gecko) Chrome/91.0.4472.124 Safari/537.36' } all_scraping_results = [] print("\nðŸ” SCRAPING HISTORICAL SOURCES:") print("=" * 60) for i, url in enumerate(target_urls, 1): print(f"\nScraping {i}/{len(target_urls)}: {url}") print("-" * 80) try: # Make request with timeout response = requests.get(url, headers=headers, timeout=30) response.raise_for_status() # Parse HTML content soup = BeautifulSoup(response.content, 'html.parser') # Remove script and style elements for script in soup(["script", "style"]): script.decompose() # Get text content text_content = soup.get_text() # Clean up text lines = (line.strip() for line in text_content.splitlines()) chunks = (phrase.strip() for line in lines for phrase in line.split(" ")) clean_text = ' '.join(chunk for chunk in chunks if chunk) print(f"âœ… Successfully scraped: {url}") print(f"Content length: {len(clean_text)} characters") # Search for key terms in the content content_lower = clean_text.lower() key_terms = { '1933': len(re.findall(r'1933', content_lower)), 'tunnel': len(re.findall(r'tunnel', content_lower)), 'escape': len(re.findall(r'escape', content_lower)), 'webbed feet': len(re.findall(r'webbed feet', content_lower)), 'webbed': len(re.findall(r'webbed', content_lower)), 'execution': len(re.findall(r'execution', content_lower)), 'executed': len(re.findall(r'executed', content_lower)), 'electric chair': len(re.findall(r'electric chair', content_lower)), 'michigan city': len(re.findall(r'michigan city', content_lower)), 'utility': len(re.findall(r'utility', content_lower)), 'ancient': len(re.findall(r'ancient', content_lower)), 'prison break': len(re.findall(r'prison break', content_lower)), 'death sentence': len(re.findall(r'death sentence', content_lower)) } total_matches = sum(key_terms.values()) print(f"Key term matches found: {total_matches}") if total_matches > 0: print(f"ðŸŽ¯ RELEVANT CONTENT FOUND:") for term, count in key_terms.items(): if count > 0: print(f" - '{term}': {count} mentions") # Extract relevant sentences/paragraphs sentences = re.split(r'[.!?]+', clean_text) relevant_sentences = [] for sentence in sentences: sentence_lower = sentence.lower().strip() if len(sentence_lower) > 20: # Skip very short sentences # Check if sentence contains our key terms if any(term in sentence_lower for term in ['1933', 'tunnel', 'escape', 'webbed', 'execution', 'michigan city']): relevant_sentences.append(sentence.strip()) if relevant_sentences: print(f"\nðŸ“„ RELEVANT CONTENT EXCERPTS:") for j, sentence in enumerate(relevant_sentences[:5], 1): # Show top 5 print(f"\n{j}. {sentence[:400]}{'...' if len(sentence) > 400 else ''}") print("-" * 40) # Special search for webbed feet references webbed_context = [] words = clean_text.split() for idx, word in enumerate(words): if 'webbed' in word.lower(): # Get context around the word (10 words before and after) start_idx = max(0, idx - 10) end_idx = min(len(words), idx + 11) context = ' '.join(words[start_idx:end_idx]) webbed_context.append(context) if webbed_context: print(f"\nðŸ‘£ WEBBED FEET CONTEXT:") for context in webbed_context[:3]: print(f"Context: {context}") print("-" * 30) # Store scraping result all_scraping_results.append({ 'url': url, 'success': True, 'content_length': len(clean_text), 'key_term_matches': key_terms, 'total_matches': total_matches, 'relevant_sentences': relevant_sentences[:10] if 'relevant_sentences' in locals() else [], 'webbed_context': webbed_context if 'webbed_context' in locals() else [], 'sample_content': clean_text[:1500] # Store first 1500 chars for analysis }) except requests.exceptions.RequestException as e: print(f"âŒ Request failed for {url}: {str(e)}") all_scraping_results.append({ 'url': url, 'success': False, 'error': f"Request error: {str(e)}" }) except Exception as e: print(f"âŒ Error scraping {url}: {str(e)}") all_scraping_results.append({ 'url': url, 'success': False, 'error': f"General error: {str(e)}" }) # Small delay between requests to be respectful time.sleep(2) print("\n" + "=" * 90) # Save scraping results timestamp = datetime.now().strftime("%Y%m%d_%H%M%S") results_file = f"workspace/indiana_prison_1933_scraping_results_{timestamp}.json" with open(results_file, 'w', encoding='utf-8') as f: json.dump({ 'scraping_timestamp': datetime.now().isoformat(), 'search_method': 'basic_web_scraping_requests_beautifulsoup', 'search_focus': '1933 Indiana State Prison tunnel escape, webbed feet prisoners, executions, execution injuries', 'total_urls_attempted': len(target_urls), 'successful_scrapes': len([r for r in all_scraping_results if r.get('success', False)]), 'scraping_results': all_scraping_results }, f, indent=2, ensure_ascii=False) print(f"\n\nðŸ“Š SCRAPING OPERATION SUMMARY:") print(f"Total URLs attempted: {len(target_urls)}") print(f"Successful scrapes: {len([r for r in all_scraping_results if r.get('success', False)])}") print(f"Scraping results saved to: {results_file}") # Analyze the scraped content for our specific targets print("\n\nðŸŽ¯ ANALYZING SCRAPED CONTENT FOR TARGET INFORMATION:") print("=" * 70) # Categorize findings highly_relevant_results = [] tunnel_escape_findings = [] webbed_feet_findings = [] execution_findings = [] 1933_findings = [] for result in all_scraping_results: if result.get('success') and result.get('total_matches', 0) > 3: highly_relevant_results.append(result) if result.get('success'): key_matches = result.get('key_term_matches', {}) # import requests from bs4 import BeautifulSoup import json from datetime import datetime import time import re print("Starting basic web scraping for 1933 Indiana State Prison tunnel escape...") print("Target: Individuals with webbed feet, tunnel escape, ancient utility system, executions") print("Method: Direct web scraping using requests and BeautifulSoup") print("=" * 90) # Define target URLs for historical prison information target_urls = [ "https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Indiana_State_Prison", "https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/List_of_prison_escapes", "https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/John_Dillinger", "https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Michigan_City,_Indiana", "https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/List_of_people_executed_in_Indiana" ] # Set up headers to avoid blocking headers = { 'User-Agent': 'Mozilla/5.0 (Windows NT 10.0; Win64; x64) AppleWebKit/537.36 (KHTML, like Gecko) Chrome/91.0.4472.124 Safari/537.36' } all_scraping_results = [] print("\nðŸ” SCRAPING HISTORICAL SOURCES:") print("=" * 60) for i, url in enumerate(target_urls, 1): print(f"\nScraping {i}/{len(target_urls)}: {url}") print("-" * 80) try: # Make request with timeout response = requests.get(url, headers=headers, timeout=30) response.raise_for_status() # Parse HTML content soup = BeautifulSoup(response.content, 'html.parser') # Remove script and style elements for script in soup(["script", "style"]): script.decompose() # Get text content text_content = soup.get_text() # Clean up text lines = (line.strip() for line in text_content.splitlines()) chunks = (phrase.strip() for line in lines for phrase in line.split(" ")) clean_text = ' '.join(chunk for chunk in chunks if chunk) print(f"âœ… Successfully scraped: {url}") print(f"Content length: {len(clean_text)} characters") # Search for key terms in the content content_lower = clean_text.lower() key_terms = { '1933': len(re.findall(r'1933', content_lower)), 'tunnel': len(re.findall(r'tunnel', content_lower)), 'escape': len(re.findall(r'escape', content_lower)), 'webbed feet': len(re.findall(r'webbed feet', content_lower)), 'webbed': len(re.findall(r'webbed', content_lower)), 'execution': len(re.findall(r'execution', content_lower)), 'executed': len(re.findall(r'executed', content_lower)), 'electric chair': len(re.findall(r'electric chair', content_lower)), 'michigan city': len(re.findall(r'michigan city', content_lower)), 'utility': len(re.findall(r'utility', content_lower)), 'ancient': len(re.findall(r'ancient', content_lower)), 'prison break': len(re.findall(r'prison break', content_lower)), 'death sentence': len(re.findall(r'death sentence', content_lower)) } total_matches = sum(key_terms.values()) print(f"Key term matches found: {total_matches}") if total_matches > 0: print(f"ðŸŽ¯ RELEVANT CONTENT FOUND:") for term, count in key_terms.items(): if count > 0: print(f" - '{term}': {count} mentions") # Extract relevant sentences/paragraphs sentences = re.split(r'[.!?]+', clean_text) relevant_sentences = [] for sentence in sentences: sentence_lower = sentence.lower().strip() if len(sentence_lower) > 20: # Skip very short sentences # Check if sentence contains our key terms if any(term in sentence_lower for term in ['1933', 'tunnel', 'escape', 'webbed', 'execution', 'michigan city']): relevant_sentences.append(sentence.strip()) if relevant_sentences: print(f"\nðŸ“„ RELEVANT CONTENT EXCERPTS:") for j, sentence in enumerate(relevant_sentences[:5], 1): # Show top 5 print(f"\n{j}. {sentence[:400]}{'...' if len(sentence) > 400 else ''}") print("-" * 40) # Special search for webbed feet references webbed_context = [] words = clean_text.split() for idx, word in enumerate(words): if 'webbed' in word.lower(): # Get context around the word (10 words before and after) start_idx = max(0, idx - 10) end_idx = min(len(words), idx + 11) context = ' '.join(words[start_idx:end_idx]) webbed_context.append(context) if webbed_context: print(f"\nðŸ‘£ WEBBED FEET CONTEXT:") for context in webbed_context[:3]: print(f"Context: {context}") print("-" * 30) # Store scraping result all_scraping_results.append({ 'url': url, 'success': True, 'content_length': len(clean_text), 'key_term_matches': key_terms, 'total_matches': total_matches, 'relevant_sentences': relevant_sentences[:10] if 'relevant_sentences' in locals() else [], 'webbed_context': webbed_context if 'webbed_context' in locals() else [], 'sample_content': clean_text[:1500] # Store first 1500 chars for analysis }) except requests.exceptions.RequestException as e: print(f"âŒ Request failed for {url}: {str(e)}") all_scraping_results.append({ 'url': url, 'success': False, 'error': f"Request error: {str(e)}" }) except Exception as e: print(f"âŒ Error scraping {url}: {str(e)}") all_scraping_results.append({ 'url': url, 'success': False, 'error': f"General error: {str(e)}" }) # Small delay between requests to be respectful time.sleep(2) print("\n" + "=" * 90) # Save scraping results timestamp = datetime.now().strftime("%Y%m%d_%H%M%S") results_file = f"workspace/indiana_prison_1933_scraping_results_{timestamp}.json" with open(results_file, 'w', encoding='utf-8') as f: json.dump({ 'scraping_timestamp': datetime.now().isoformat(), 'search_method': 'basic_web_scraping_requests_beautifulsoup', 'search_focus': '1933 Indiana State Prison tunnel escape, webbed feet prisoners, executions, execution injuries', 'total_urls_attempted': len(target_urls), 'successful_scrapes': len([r for r in all_scraping_results if r.get('success', False)]), 'scraping_results': all_scraping_results }, f, indent=2, ensure_ascii=False) print(f"\n\nðŸ“Š SCRAPING OPERATION SUMMARY:") print(f"Total URLs attempted: {len(target_urls)}") print(f"Successful scrapes: {len([r for r in all_scraping_results if r.get('success', False)])}") print(f"Scraping results saved to: {results_file}") # Analyze the scraped content for our specific targets print("\n\nðŸŽ¯ ANALYZING SCRAPED CONTENT FOR TARGET INFORMATION:") print("=" * 70) # Categorize findings highly_relevant_results = [] tunnel_escape_findings = [] webbed_feet_findings = [] execution_findings = [] 1933_findings = [] for result in all_scraping_results: if result.get('success') and result.get('total_matches', 0) > 3: highly_relevant_results.append(result) if result.get('success'): key_matches = result.get('key_term_matches', {}) # import requests from bs4 import BeautifulSoup import json from datetime import datetime import time import re print("Starting basic web scraping for 1933 Indiana State Prison tunnel escape...") print("Target: Individuals with webbed feet, tunnel escape, ancient utility system, executions") print("Method: Direct web scraping using requests and BeautifulSoup") print("=" * 90) # Define target URLs for historical prison information target_urls = [ "https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Indiana_State_Prison", "https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/List_of_prison_escapes", "https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/John_Dillinger", "https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Michigan_City,_Indiana", "https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/List_of_people_executed_in_Indiana" ] # Set up headers to avoid blocking headers = { 'User-Agent': 'Mozilla/5.0 (Windows NT 10.0; Win64; x64) AppleWebKit/537.36 (KHTML, like Gecko) Chrome/91.0.4472.124 Safari/537.36' } all_scraping_results = [] print("\nðŸ” SCRAPING HISTORICAL SOURCES:") print("=" * 60) for i, url in enumerate(target_urls, 1): print(f"\nScraping {i}/{len(target_urls)}: {url}") print("-" * 80) try: # Make request with timeout response = requests.get(url, headers=headers, timeout=30) response.raise_for_status() # Parse HTML content soup = BeautifulSoup(response.content, 'html.parser') # Remove script and style elements for script in soup(["script", "style"]): script.decompose() # Get text content text_content = soup.get_text() # Clean up text lines = (line.strip() for line in text_content.splitlines()) chunks = (phrase.strip() for line in lines for phrase in line.split(" ")) clean_text = ' '.join(chunk for chunk in chunks if chunk) print(f"âœ… Successfully scraped: {url}") print(f"Content length: {len(clean_text)} characters") # Search for key terms in the content content_lower = clean_text.lower() key_terms = { '1933': len(re.findall(r'1933', content_lower)), 'tunnel': len(re.findall(r'tunnel', content_lower)), 'escape': len(re.findall(r'escape', content_lower)), 'webbed feet': len(re.findall(r'webbed feet', content_lower)), 'webbed': len(re.findall(r'webbed', content_lower)), 'execution': len(re.findall(r'execution', content_lower)), 'executed': len(re.findall(r'executed', content_lower)), 'electric chair': len(re.findall(r'electric chair', content_lower)), 'michigan city': len(re.findall(r'michigan city', content_lower)), 'utility': len(re.findall(r'utility', content_lower)), 'ancient': len(re.findall(r'ancient', content_lower)), 'prison break': len(re.findall(r'prison break', content_lower)), 'death sentence': len(re.findall(r'death sentence', content_lower)) } total_matches = sum(key_terms.values()) print(f"Key term matches found: {total_matches}") if total_matches > 0: print(f"ðŸŽ¯ RELEVANT CONTENT FOUND:") for term, count in key_terms.items(): if count > 0: print(f" - '{term}': {count} mentions") # Extract relevant sentences/paragraphs sentences = re.split(r'[.!?]+', clean_text) relevant_sentences = [] for sentence in sentences: sentence_lower = sentence.lower().strip() if len(sentence_lower) > 20: # Skip very short sentences # Check if sentence contains our key terms if any(term in sentence_lower for term in ['1933', 'tunnel', 'escape', 'webbed', 'execution', 'michigan city']): relevant_sentences.append(sentence.strip()) if relevant_sentences: print(f"\nðŸ“„ RELEVANT CONTENT EXCERPTS:") for j, sentence in enumerate(relevant_sentences[:5], 1): # Show top 5 print(f"\n{j}. {sentence[:400]{'...' if len(sentence) > 400 else ''}}") print("-" * 40) # Special search for webbed feet references webbed_context = [] words = clean_text.split() for idx, word in enumerate(words): if 'webbed' in word.lower(): # Get context around the word (10 words before and after) start_idx = max(0, idx - 10) end_idx = min(len(words), idx + 11) context = ' '.join(words[start_idx:end_idx]) webbed_context.append(context) if webbed_context: print(f"\nðŸ‘£ WEBBED FEET CONTEXT:") for context in webbed_context[:3]: print(f"Context: {context}") print("-" * 30) # Store scraping result all_scraping_results.append({ 'url': url, 'success': True, 'content_length': len(clean_text), 'key_term_matches': key_terms, 'total_matches': total_matches, 'relevant_sentences': relevant_sentences[:10] if 'relevant_sentences' in locals() else [], 'webbed_context': webbed_context if 'webbed_context' in locals() else [], 'sample_content': clean_text[:1500] # Store first 1500 chars for analysis }) except requests.exceptions.RequestException as e: print(f"âŒ Request failed for {url}: {str(e)}") all_scraping_results.append({ 'url': url, 'success': False, 'error': f"Request error: {str(e)}" }) except Exception as e: print(f"âŒ Error scraping {url}: {str(e)}") all_scraping_results.append({ 'url': url, 'success': False, 'error': f"General error: {str(e)}" }) # import requests from bs4 import BeautifulSoup import json from datetime import datetime import time import re print("Starting web scraping for 1933 Indiana State Prison tunnel escape...") print("Target: Individuals with webbed feet, tunnel escape, ancient utility system, executions") print("Method: Direct web scraping using requests and BeautifulSoup") print("=" * 90) # Define target URLs for historical prison information target_urls = [ "https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Indiana_State_Prison", "https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/List_of_prison_escapes", "https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/John_Dillinger", "https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Michigan_City,_Indiana", "https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/List_of_people_executed_in_Indiana" ] # Set up headers to avoid blocking headers = { 'User-Agent': 'Mozilla/5.0 (Windows NT 10.0; Win64; x64) AppleWebKit/537.36 (KHTML, like Gecko) Chrome/91.0.4472.124 Safari/537.36' } all_scraping_results = [] print("\nðŸ” SCRAPING HISTORICAL SOURCES:") print("=" * 60) for i, url in enumerate(target_urls, 1): print(f"\nScraping {i}/{len(target_urls)}: {url}") print("-" * 80) try: # Make request with timeout response = requests.get(url, headers=headers, timeout=30) response.raise_for_status() # Parse HTML content soup = BeautifulSoup(response.content, 'html.parser') # Remove script and style elements for script in soup(["script", "style"]): script.decompose() # Get text content text_content = soup.get_text() # Clean up text lines = (line.strip() for line in text_content.splitlines()) chunks = (phrase.strip() for line in lines for phrase in line.split(" ")) clean_text = ' '.join(chunk for chunk in chunks if chunk) print(f"âœ… Successfully scraped: {url}") print(f"Content length: {len(clean_text)} characters") # Search for key terms in the content content_lower = clean_text.lower() key_terms = { '1933': len(re.findall(r'1933', content_lower)), 'tunnel': len(re.findall(r'tunnel', content_lower)), 'escape': len(re.findall(r'escape', content_lower)), 'webbed feet': len(re.findall(r'webbed feet', content_lower)), 'webbed': len(re.findall(r'webbed', content_lower)), 'execution': len(re.findall(r'execution', content_lower)), 'executed': len(re.findall(r'executed', content_lower)), 'electric chair': len(re.findall(r'electric chair', content_lower)), 'michigan city': len(re.findall(r'michigan city', content_lower)), 'utility': len(re.findall(r'utility', content_lower)), 'ancient': len(re.findall(r'ancient', content_lower)), 'prison break': len(re.findall(r'prison break', content_lower)), 'death sentence': len(re.findall(r'death sentence', content_lower)) } total_matches = sum(key_terms.values()) print(f"Key term matches found: {total_matches}") if total_matches > 0: print(f"ðŸŽ¯ RELEVANT CONTENT FOUND:") for term, count in key_terms.items(): if count > 0: print(f" - '{term}': {count} mentions") # Extract relevant sentences/paragraphs sentences = re.split(r'[.!?]+', clean_text) relevant_sentences = [] for sentence in sentences: sentence_lower = sentence.lower().strip() if len(sentence_lower) > 20: # Skip very short sentences # Check if sentence contains our key terms if any(term in sentence_lower for term in ['1933', 'tunnel', 'escape', 'webbed', 'execution', 'michigan city']): relevant_sentences.append(sentence.strip()) if relevant_sentences: print(f"\nðŸ“„ RELEVANT CONTENT EXCERPTS:") for j, sentence in enumerate(relevant_sentences[:5], 1): # Show top 5 # FIXED: Corrected f-string syntax excerpt = sentence[:400] if len(sentence) > 400: excerpt += "..." print(f"\n{j}. {excerpt}") print("-" * 40) # Special search for webbed feet references webbed_context = [] words = clean_text.split() for idx, word in enumerate(words): if 'webbed' in word.lower(): # Get context around the word (10 words before and after) start_idx = max(0, idx - 10) end_idx = min(len(words), idx + 11) context = ' '.join(words[start_idx:end_idx]) webbed_context.append(context) if webbed_context: print(f"\nðŸ‘£ WEBBED FEET CONTEXT:") for context in webbed_context[:3]: print(f"Context: {context}") print("-" * 30) # Store scraping result all_scraping_results.append({ 'url': url, 'success': True, 'content_length': len(clean_text), 'key_term_matches': key_terms, 'total_matches': total_matches, 'relevant_sentences': relevant_sentences[:10] if 'relevant_sentences' in locals() else [], 'webbed_context': webbed_context if 'webbed_context' in locals() else [], 'sample_content': clean_text[:1500] # Store first 1500 chars for analysis }) except requests.exceptions.RequestException as e: print(f"âŒ Request failed for {url}: {str(e)}") all_scraping_results.append({ 'url': url, 'success': False, 'error': f"Request error: {str(e)}" }) except Exception as e: print(f"âŒ Error scraping {url}: {str(e)}") all_scraping_results.append({ 'url': url, 'success': False, 'error': f"General error: {str(e)}" }) # Small delay between requests to be respectful time.sleep(2) print("\n" + "=" * 90) # Save scraping results timestamp = datetime.now().strftime("%Y%m%d_%H%M%S") results_file = f"workspace/indiana_prison_1933_scraping_results_{timestamp}.json" with open(results_file, 'w', encoding='utf-8') as f: json.dump({ 'scraping_timestamp': datetime.now().isoformat(), 'search_method': 'basic_web_scraping_requests_beautifulsoup', 'search_focus': '1933 Indiana State Prison tunnel escape, webbed feet prisoners, executions, execution injuries', 'total_urls_attempted': len(target_urls), 'successful_scrapes': len([r for r in all_scraping_results if r.get('success', False)]), 'scraping_results': all_scraping_results }, f, indent=2, ensure_ascii=False) print(f"\n\nðŸ“Š SCRAPING OPERATION SUMMARY:") print(f"Total URLs attempted: {len(target_urls)}") print(f"Successful scrapes: {len([r for r in all_scraping_results if r.get('success', False)])}") print(f"Scraping results saved to: {results_file}") # Analyze the scraped content for our specific targets print("\n\nðŸŽ¯ ANALYZING SCRAPED CONTENT FOR TARGET INFORMATION:") print("=" * 70) # Categorize findings - Using valid Python variable names highly_relevant_results = [] tunnel_escape_findings = [] webbed_feet_findings = [] execution_findings = [] year_1933_findings = [] for result in all_scraping_results: if result.get('success') and result.get('total_matches', 0) > 3: highly_relevant_results.append(result) if result.get('success'): key_matches = result.get('key_term_matches', {}) # Check for specific findings if key_matches.get('tunnel', 0) > 0 and (key_matches.get('escape', 0) > 0 or key_matches.get('prison break', 0) > 0): tunnel_escape_findings.append(result) if key_matches.get('webbed feet', 0) > 0 or key_matches.get('webbed', 0) > 0: webbed_feet_findings.append(result) if key_matches.get('execution', 0) > 0 or key_matches.get('executed', 0) > 0 or key_matches.get('electric chair', 0) > 0: execution_findings.append(result) if key_matches.get('1933', 0) > 0: year_1933_findings.append(result) print(f"\nðŸ“‹ ANALYSIS RESULTS:") print(f"Highly relevant sources (3+ matches): {len(highly_relevant_results)}") print(f"Tunnel escape references: {len(tunnel_escape_findings)}") print(f"Webbed feet references: {len(webbed_feet_findings)}") print(f"Execution references: {len(execution_findings)}") print(f"1933 references: {len(year_1933_findings)}") # Display key findings if highly_relevant_results: print(f"\nðŸŽ¯ MOST RELEVANT SOURCES FOUND:") for i, result in enumerate(highly_relevant_results, 1): print(f"\n{i}. Source: {result['url']}") print(f" Total key term matches: {result.get('total_matches', 0)}") key_matches = result.get('key_term_matches', {}) significant_matches = {k: v for k, v in key_matches.items() if v > 0} print(f" Key terms found: {significant_matches}") if result.get('relevant_sentences'): sample_content = result['relevant_sentences'][0][:200] print(f" Sample relevant content: {sample_content}...") if webbed_feet_findings: print(f"\nðŸ‘£ WEBBED FEET REFERENCES FOUND:") for result in webbed_feet_findings: print(f"\n- Source: {result['url']}") webbed_mentions = result.get('key_term_matches', {}).get('webbed', 0) webbed_feet_mentions = result.get('key_term_matches', {}).get('webbed feet', 0) print(f" 'webbed' mentions: {webbed_mentions}, 'webbed feet' mentions: {webbed_feet_mentions}") if result.get('webbed_context'): context_sample = result['webbed_context'][0][:300] print(f" Context: {context_sample}...") if year_1933_findings: print(f"\nðŸ“… 1933 REFERENCES FOUND:") for result in year_1933_findings: print(f"\n- Source: {result['url']}") print(f" '1933' mentions: {result.get('key_term_matches', {}).get('1933', 0)}") # Look for 1933 context in relevant sentences relevant_1933_sentences = [] for sentence in result.get('relevant_sentences', []): if '1933' in sentence: relevant_1933_sentences.append(sentence) if relevant_1933_sentences: context_1933 = relevant_1933_sentences[0][:300] print(f" 1933 context: {context_1933}...") # Look for specific combinations that might indicate our target event print("\n\nðŸ” SEARCHING FOR SPECIFIC EVENT COMBINATIONS:") print("=" * 60) # Check for results that mention both 1933 AND tunnel/escape event_candidates = [] for result in all_scraping_results: if result.get('success'): key_matches = result.get('key_term_matches', {}) if (key_matches.get('1933', 0) > 0 and (key_matches.get('tunnel', 0) > 0 or key_matches.get('escape', 0) > 0) and key_matches.get('michigan city', 0) > 0): event_candidates.append(result) if event_candidates: print(f"\nðŸŽ¯ POTENTIAL 1933 TUNNEL ESCAPE EVENT CANDIDATES:") for i, result in enumerate(event_candidates, 1): print(f"\n{i}. Source: {result['url']}") print(f" 1933 mentions: {result.get('key_term_matches', {}).get('1933', 0)}") print(f" Tunnel mentions: {result.get('key_term_matches', {}).get('tunnel', 0)}") print(f" Escape mentions: {result.get('key_term_matches', {}).get('escape', 0)}") print(f" Michigan City mentions: {result.get('key_term_matches', {}).get('michigan city', 0)}") # Show relevant sentences that might describe the event event_sentences = [] for sentence in result.get('relevant_sentences', []): sentence_lower = sentence.lower() if '1933' in sentence_lower and ('tunnel' in sentence_lower or 'escape' in sentence_lower): event_sentences.append(sentence) if event_sentences: print(f"\n ðŸ” POTENTIAL EVENT DESCRIPTIONS:") for j, sentence in enumerate(event_sentences[:2], 1): event_desc = sentence[:400] if len(sentence) > 400: event_desc += "..." print(f" {j}. {event_desc}") else: print("\nâš ï¸ No direct matches found for 1933 + tunnel + escape + Michigan City combination") print(" This might indicate the specific event details are not in these general sources") print(" May need to search more specialized historical prison records or newspaper archives") # Create comprehensive analysis summary analysis_file = 'workspace/indiana_prison_1933_scraping_analysis.txt' with open(analysis_file, 'w', encoding='utf-8') as f: f.write("1933 INDIANA STATE PRISON TUNNEL ESCAPE - WEB SCRAPING ANALYSIS\n") f.write("=" * 65 + "\n\n") f.write(f"Analysis conducted: {datetime.now().strftime('%Y-%m-%d %H:%M:%S')}\n") f.write(f"Search method: Basic web scraping with requests and BeautifulSoup\n") f.write(f"Total URLs scraped: {len(target_urls)}\n") f.write(f"Successful scrapes: {len([r for r in all_scraping_results if r.get('success', False)])}\n\n") f.write("SEARCH OBJECTIVES STATUS:\n") f.write("1. import requests from bs4 import BeautifulSoup import json from datetime import datetime import time import re print("Starting comprehensive web search for 1933 Indiana State Prison tunnel escape...") print("Target: Individuals with webbed feet, tunnel escape, ancient utility system, executions") print("Method: Direct web scraping using requests and BeautifulSoup") print("=" * 90) # Define target URLs for historical prison information target_urls = [ "https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Indiana_State_Prison", "https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/List_of_prison_escapes", "https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/John_Dillinger", "https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Michigan_City,_Indiana", "https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/List_of_people_executed_in_Indiana" ] # Set up headers to avoid blocking headers = { 'User-Agent': 'Mozilla/5.0 (Windows NT 10.0; Win64; x64) AppleWebKit/537.36 (KHTML, like Gecko) Chrome/91.0.4472.124 Safari/537.36' } all_scraping_results = [] print("\nðŸ” SCRAPING HISTORICAL SOURCES:") print("=" * 60) for i, url in enumerate(target_urls, 1): print(f"\nScraping {i}/{len(target_urls)}: {url}") print("-" * 80) try: # Make request with timeout response = requests.get(url, headers=headers, timeout=30) response.raise_for_status() # Parse HTML content soup = BeautifulSoup(response.content, 'html.parser') # Remove script and style elements for script in soup(["script", "style"]): script.decompose() # Get text content text_content = soup.get_text() # Clean up text lines = (line.strip() for line in text_content.splitlines()) chunks = (phrase.strip() for line in lines for phrase in line.split(" ")) clean_text = ' '.join(chunk for chunk in chunks if chunk) print(f"âœ… Successfully scraped: {url}") print(f"Content length: {len(clean_text)} characters") # Search for key terms in the content content_lower = clean_text.lower() key_terms = { '1933': len(re.findall(r'1933', content_lower)), 'tunnel': len(re.findall(r'tunnel', content_lower)), 'escape': len(re.findall(r'escape', content_lower)), 'webbed feet': len(re.findall(r'webbed feet', content_lower)), 'webbed': len(re.findall(r'webbed', content_lower)), 'execution': len(re.findall(r'execution', content_lower)), 'executed': len(re.findall(r'executed', content_lower)), 'electric chair': len(re.findall(r'electric chair', content_lower)), 'michigan city': len(re.findall(r'michigan city', content_lower)), 'utility': len(re.findall(r'utility', content_lower)), 'ancient': len(re.findall(r'ancient', content_lower)), 'prison break': len(re.findall(r'prison break', content_lower)), 'death sentence': len(re.findall(r'death sentence', content_lower)) } total_matches = sum(key_terms.values()) print(f"Key term matches found: {total_matches}") if total_matches > 0: print(f"ðŸŽ¯ RELEVANT CONTENT FOUND:") for term, count in key_terms.items(): if count > 0: print(f" - '{term}': {count} mentions") # Extract relevant sentences/paragraphs sentences = re.split(r'[.!?]+', clean_text) relevant_sentences = [] for sentence in sentences: sentence_lower = sentence.lower().strip() if len(sentence_lower) > 20: # Skip very short sentences # Check if sentence contains our key terms if any(term in sentence_lower for term in ['1933', 'tunnel', 'escape', 'webbed', 'execution', 'michigan city']): relevant_sentences.append(sentence.strip()) if relevant_sentences: print(f"\nðŸ“„ RELEVANT CONTENT EXCERPTS:") for j, sentence in enumerate(relevant_sentences[:5], 1): # Show top 5 # Fixed f-string syntax by separating the conditional logic excerpt = sentence[:400] if len(sentence) > 400: excerpt = excerpt + "..." print(f"\n{j}. {excerpt}") print("-" * 40) # Special search for webbed feet references webbed_context = [] words = clean_text.split() for idx, word in enumerate(words): if 'webbed' in word.lower(): # Get context around the word (10 words before and after) start_idx = max(0, idx - 10) end_idx = min(len(words), idx + 11) context = ' '.join(words[start_idx:end_idx]) webbed_context.append(context) if webbed_context: print(f"\nðŸ‘£ WEBBED FEET CONTEXT:") for context in webbed_context[:3]: print(f"Context: {context}") print("-" * 30) # Store scraping result all_scraping_results.append({ 'url': url, 'success': True, 'content_length': len(clean_text), 'key_term_matches': key_terms, 'total_matches': total_matches, 'relevant_sentences': relevant_sentences[:10] if 'relevant_sentences' in locals() else [], 'webbed_context': webbed_context if 'webbed_context' in locals() else [], 'sample_content': clean_text[:1500] # Store first 1500 chars for analysis }) except requests.exceptions.RequestException as e: print(f"âŒ Request failed for {url}: {str(e)}") all_scraping_results.append({ 'url': url, 'success': False, 'error': f"Request error: {str(e)}" }) except Exception as e: print(f"âŒ Error scraping {url}: {str(e)}") all_scraping_results.append({ 'url': url, 'success': False, 'error': f"General error: {str(e)}" }) # Small delay between requests to be respectful time.sleep(3) print("\n" + "=" * 90) # Save scraping results timestamp = datetime.now().strftime("%Y%m%d_%H%M%S") results_file = f"workspace/indiana_prison_1933_scraping_results_{timestamp}.json" with open(results_file, 'w', encoding='utf-8') as f: json.dump({ 'scraping_timestamp': datetime.now().isoformat(), 'search_method': 'basic_web_scraping_requests_beautifulsoup', 'search_focus': '1933 Indiana State Prison tunnel escape, webbed feet prisoners, executions, execution injuries', 'total_urls_attempted': len(target_urls), 'successful_scrapes': len([r for r in all_scraping_results if r.get('success', False)]), 'scraping_results': all_scraping_results }, f, indent=2, ensure_ascii=False) print(f"\n\nðŸ“Š SCRAPING OPERATION SUMMARY:") print(f"Total URLs attempted: {len(target_urls)}") print(f"Successful scrapes: {len([r for r in all_scraping_results if r.get('success', False)])}") print(f"Scraping results saved to: {results_file}") # import requests from bs4 import BeautifulSoup import json from datetime import datetime import time import re print("Starting comprehensive web search for 1933 Indiana State Prison tunnel escape...") print("Target: Individuals with webbed feet, tunnel escape, ancient utility system, executions") print("Method: Direct web scraping using requests and BeautifulSoup") print("=" * 90) # Define target URLs for historical prison information target_urls = [ "https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Indiana_State_Prison", "https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/List_of_prison_escapes", "https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/John_Dillinger", "https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Michigan_City,_Indiana", "https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/List_of_people_executed_in_Indiana" ] # Set up headers to avoid blocking headers = { 'User-Agent': 'Mozilla/5.0 (Windows NT 10.0; Win64; x64) AppleWebKit/537.36 (KHTML, like Gecko) Chrome/91.0.4472.124 Safari/537.36' } all_scraping_results = [] print("\nðŸ” SCRAPING HISTORICAL SOURCES:") print("=" * 60) for i, url in enumerate(target_urls, 1): print(f"\nScraping {i}/{len(target_urls)}: {url}") print("-" * 80) try: # Make request with timeout response = requests.get(url, headers=headers, timeout=30) response.raise_for_status() # Parse HTML content soup = BeautifulSoup(response.content, 'html.parser') # Remove script and style elements for script in soup(["script", "style"]): script.decompose() # Get text content text_content = soup.get_text() # Clean up text lines = (line.strip() for line in text_content.splitlines()) chunks = (phrase.strip() for line in lines for phrase in line.split(" ")) clean_text = ' '.join(chunk for chunk in chunks if chunk) print(f"âœ… Successfully scraped: {url}") print(f"Content length: {len(clean_text)} characters") # Search for key terms in the content content_lower = clean_text.lower() key_terms = { '1933': len(re.findall(r'1933', content_lower)), 'tunnel': len(re.findall(r'tunnel', content_lower)), 'escape': len(re.findall(r'escape', content_lower)), 'webbed feet': len(re.findall(r'webbed feet', content_lower)), 'webbed': len(re.findall(r'webbed', content_lower)), 'execution': len(re.findall(r'execution', content_lower)), 'executed': len(re.findall(r'executed', content_lower)), 'electric chair': len(re.findall(r'electric chair', content_lower)), 'michigan city': len(re.findall(r'michigan city', content_lower)), 'utility': len(re.findall(r'utility', content_lower)), 'ancient': len(re.findall(r'ancient', content_lower)), 'prison break': len(re.findall(r'prison break', content_lower)), 'death sentence': len(re.findall(r'death sentence', content_lower)) } total_matches = sum(key_terms.values()) print(f"Key term matches found: {total_matches}") if total_matches > 0: print(f"ðŸŽ¯ RELEVANT CONTENT FOUND:") for term, count in key_terms.items(): if count > 0: print(f" - '{term}': {count} mentions") # Extract relevant sentences/paragraphs sentences = re.split(r'[.!?]+', clean_text) relevant_sentences = [] for sentence in sentences: sentence_lower = sentence.lower().strip() if len(sentence_lower) > 20: # Skip very short sentences # Check if sentence contains our key terms if any(term in sentence_lower for term in ['1933', 'tunnel', 'escape', 'webbed', 'execution', 'michigan city']): relevant_sentences.append(sentence.strip()) if relevant_sentences: print(f"\nðŸ“„ RELEVANT CONTENT EXCERPTS:") for j, sentence in enumerate(relevant_sentences[:5], 1): # Show top 5 # Fixed f-string syntax by separating the conditional logic excerpt = sentence[:400] if len(sentence) > 400: excerpt = excerpt + "..." print(f"\n{j}. {excerpt}") print("-" * 40) # Special search for webbed feet references webbed_context = [] words = clean_text.split() for idx, word in enumerate(words): if 'webbed' in word.lower(): # Get context around the word (10 words before and after) start_idx = max(0, idx - 10) end_idx = min(len(words), idx + 11) context = ' '.join(words[start_idx:end_idx]) webbed_context.append(context) if webbed_context: print(f"\nðŸ‘£ WEBBED FEET CONTEXT:") for context in webbed_context[:3]: print(f"Context: {context}") print("-" * 30) # Store scraping result all_scraping_results.append({ 'url': url, 'success': True, 'content_length': len(clean_text), 'key_term_matches': key_terms, 'total_matches': total_matches, 'relevant_sentences': relevant_sentences[:10] if 'relevant_sentences' in locals() else [], 'webbed_context': webbed_context if 'webbed_context' in locals() else [], 'sample_content': clean_text[:1500] # Store first 1500 chars for analysis }) except requests.exceptions.RequestException as e: print(f"âŒ Request failed for {url}: {str(e)}") all_scraping_results.append({ 'url': url, 'success': False, 'error': f"Request error: {str(e)}" }) except Exception as e: print(f"âŒ Error scraping {url}: {str(e)}") all_scraping_results.append({ 'url': url, 'success': False, 'error': f"General error: {str(e)}" }) # Small delay between requests to be respectful time.sleep(3) print("\n" + "=" * 90) # Save scraping results timestamp = datetime.now().strftime("%Y%m%d_%H%M%S") results_file = f"workspace/indiana_prison_1933_scraping_results_{timestamp}.json" with open(results_file, 'w', encoding='utf-8') as f: json.dump({ 'scraping_timestamp': datetime.now().isoformat(), 'search_method': 'basic_web_scraping_requests_beautifulsoup', 'search_focus': '1933 Indiana State Prison tunnel escape, webbed feet prisoners, executions, execution injuries', 'total_urls_attempted': len(target_urls), 'successful_scrapes': len([r for r in all_scraping_results if r.get('success', False)]), 'scraping_results': all_scraping_results }, f, indent=2, ensure_ascii=False) print(f"\n\nðŸ“Š SCRAPING OPERATION SUMMARY:") print(f"Total URLs attempted: {len(target_urls)}") print(f"Successful scrapes: {len([r for r in all_scraping_results if r.get('success', False)])}") print(f"Scraping results saved to: {results_file}") # Analyze the scraped content for our specific targets print("\n\nðŸŽ¯ ANALYZING SCRAPED CONTENT FOR TARGET INFORMATION:") print("=" * 70) # Categorize findings - Using valid Python variable names highly_relevant_results = [] tunnel_escape_findings = [] webbed_feet_findings = [] execution_findings = [] year_1933_findings = [] for result in all_scraping_results: if result.get('success') and result.get('total_matches', 0) > 3: highly_relevant_results.append(result) if result.get('success'): key_matches = result.get('key_term_matches', {}) # import os import requests import json from datetime import datetime import time print("Starting comprehensive SerpAPI search for 1933 Indiana State Prison tunnel escape...") print("Target: Individuals with webbed feet, tunnel escape, ancient utility system, executions") print("Method: Using SerpAPI for targeted historical searches") print("=" * 90) # Get API key from environment api_key = os.getenv("SERPAPI_API_KEY") if api_key is None: print("âŒ Error: No SerpAPI key found in environment variables") print("Cannot proceed with web search - API key required") else: print(f"âœ… SerpAPI key found - implementing comprehensive targeted search...") print("Focus: 1933 Indiana State Prison tunnel escape with webbed feet individuals") print("=" * 90) # Define highly targeted search queries for the specific event targeted_queries = [ '"Indiana State Prison" 1933 tunnel escape "webbed feet"', '"Michigan City" prison 1933 tunnel "ancient utility system"', 'Indiana State Prison 1933 execution injuries electric chair', '"webbed feet" prisoner 1933 Indiana execution tunnel', 'Michigan City prison break 1933 utility tunnels ancient', 'Indiana State Prison tunnel escape 1933 casualties execution', '"syndactyly" prisoner 1933 Indiana State Prison', '1933 prison tunnel escape utility system Michigan City' ] print(f"\nðŸ” EXECUTING {len(targeted_queries)} TARGETED SEARCHES:") print("=" * 60) all_search_results = [] # Execute each targeted search for i, query in enumerate(targeted_queries, 1): print(f"\nSearch {i}/{len(targeted_queries)}: {query}") print("-" * 80) # Prepare API request parameters params = { "q": query, "api_key": api_key, "engine": "google", "google_domain": "google.com", "safe": "off", "num": 15, # Get more results for comprehensive coverage "type": "search" } try: # Make API request to SerpAPI response = requests.get("https://serpapi.com/search.json", params=params, timeout=30) if response.status_code == 200: results = response.json() if results.get("organic_results"): print(f"âœ… Found {len(results['organic_results'])} results for search {i}") # Process and analyze each result for j, result in enumerate(results["organic_results"], 1): title = result.get('title', 'No title') link = result.get('link', 'No link') snippet = result.get('snippet', 'No snippet') print(f"\nResult {j}:") print(f"Title: {title}") print(f"Link: {link}") print(f"Snippet: {snippet}") # Analyze relevance to our specific targets combined_text = f"{title.lower()} {snippet.lower()}" # Check for key indicators key_indicators = { 'webbed_feet': ['webbed feet', 'webbed', 'syndactyly'], 'tunnel_escape': ['tunnel', 'escape', 'breakout'], 'ancient_utility': ['utility', 'ancient', 'tunnel system', 'infrastructure'], 'execution_injuries': ['execution', 'electric chair', 'injuries', 'complications'], 'year_1933': ['1933'], 'indiana_prison': ['indiana state prison', 'michigan city'] } relevance_score = 0 matching_categories = [] for category, terms in key_indicators.items(): if any(term in combined_text for term in terms): matching_categories.append(category) relevance_score += 1 if relevance_score >= 3: print(f"ðŸŽ¯ HIGHLY RELEVANT (Score: {relevance_score}/6)") print(f"Categories: {', '.join(matching_categories)}") elif relevance_score >= 2: print(f"ðŸ“‹ RELEVANT (Score: {relevance_score}/6)") print(f"Categories: {', '.join(matching_categories)}") # Special highlighting for webbed feet mentions if any(term in combined_text for term in ['webbed feet', 'webbed', 'syndactyly']): print("ðŸ‘£ WEBBED FEET REFERENCE DETECTED!") # Special highlighting for tunnel escape mentions if 'tunnel' in combined_text and 'escape' in combined_text: print("ðŸš‡ TUNNEL ESCAPE REFERENCE DETECTED!") # Store result with analysis all_search_results.append({ 'search_number': i, 'query_text': query, 'result_number': j, 'title': title, 'link': link, 'snippet': snippet, 'relevance_score': relevance_score, 'matching_categories': matching_categories }) print("-" * 40) else: print(f"âš ï¸ No organic results found for search {i}: '{query}'") all_search_results.append({ 'search_number': i, 'query_text': query, 'result_number': 0, 'title': 'No results', 'link': 'N/A', 'snippet': 'No results found for this query', 'relevance_score': 0, 'matching_categories': [] }) else: print(f"âŒ API request failed with status {response.status_code}") if response.text: print(f"Error details: {response.text[:300]}...") except requests.exceptions.Timeout: print(f"â° Timeout occurred for search {i}. Moving to next query.") except Exception as e: print(f"âŒ Error during search {i}: {str(e)}") continue # Respectful delay between API requests time.sleep(2) print("\n" + "=" * 90) # Save comprehensive search results timestamp = datetime.now().strftime("%Y%m%d_%H%M%S") results_file = f"workspace/serpapi_1933_tunnel_escape_search_{timestamp}.json" with open(results_file, 'w', encoding='utf-8') as f: json.dump({ 'search_timestamp': datetime.now().isoformat(), 'search_method': 'serpapi_targeted_search', 'search_focus': '1933 Indiana State Prison tunnel escape - webbed feet individuals, ancient utility system, execution injuries', 'total_queries': len(targeted_queries), 'total_results': len(all_search_results), 'queries_executed': targeted_queries, 'all_search_results': all_search_results }, f, indent=2, ensure_ascii=False) print(f"\n\nðŸ“Š COMPREHENSIVE SEARCH SUMMARY:") print(f"Total targeted queries executed: {len(targeted_queries)}") print(f"Total results collected: {len(all_search_results)}") print(f"Search results saved to: {results_file}") # Analyze results for key findings print("\n\nðŸ” ANALYZING RESULTS FOR KEY FINDINGS:") print("=" * 60) # Categorize ]

all_results = []

"q": query,
"api_key": api_key,

"safe": "off",

"type": "search"
}

results = response.json()

print(f"Found {len(results['organic_results'])} results for search {i}")

print(f"Link: {link}")

'title': title,
'link': link,
'snippet': snippet
})

if sum(1 for term in key_indicators if term in combined_text) >= 3:
print("ðŸŽ¯ HIGHLY RELEVANT - Contains multiple key terms!")

print("-" * 40)
else:
print(f"No organic results found for search {i}: '{query}'")

'search_number': i,
'query_text': query,
'result_number': 0,
'title': 'No results',
'link': 'N/A',
'snippet': 'No results found for this query'
})

else:
print(f"Error: API request failed with status {response.status_code}: {response.text}")

except Exception as e:
print(f"Error during search {i}: {str(e)}")
continue

timestamp = datetime.now().strftime("%Y%m%d_%H%M%S")
results_file = f"workspace/dillinger_1933_jailbreak_search_{timestamp}.json"

with open(results_file, 'w', encoding='utf-8') as f:
json.dump({
'search_timestamp': datetime.now().isoformat(),
'search_focus': '1933 Dillinger jailbreak, fake credentials, Harry Pierpont conviction, witness testimony',
'total_queries': len(search_queries),
'total_results': len(all_results),
'queries_executed': search_queries,
'all_search_results': all_results

print(f"Keys in data: {list(data.keys())}")
print(f"Search timestamp: {data.get('search_timestamp', 'N/A')}")
print(f"Total queries: {data.get('total_queries', 'N/A')}")
print(f"Total results: {data.get('total_results', 'N/A')}")

if 'results' in data and len(data['results']) > 0:
print(f"\nFirst result structure:")
first_result = data['results'][0]
print(f"Keys in result: {list(first_result.keys())}")
print(f"Sample result preview: {first_result}")

print("\nFile structure confirmed. Proceeding with analysis...")

except json.JSONDecodeError as e:
print(f"Error reading JSON file: {e}")
print("File may be corrupted or incomplete. Will proceed with new search.")
data = None
else:
print("No existing search results file found.")
data = None

]

all_focused_results = []

for i, query in enumerate(focused_queries, 1):
print(f"\nFocused Search {i}/{len(focused_queries)}: {query}")
print("-" * 60)

params = {
"q": query,
"api_key": api_key,
"engine": "google",
"google_domain": "google.com",
"safe": "off",
"num": 10, # Reduced number for faster response
"type": "search"
}

try:
# Shorter timeout to avoid hanging
response = requests.get("https://serpapi.com/search.json", params=params, timeout=15)

if response.status_code == 200:
results = response.json()

if results.get("organic_results"):
print(f"Found {len(results['organic_results'])} results")

for j, result in enumerate(results["organic_results"], 1):
title = result.get('title', 'No title')
link = result.get('link', 'No link')
snippet = result.get('snippet', 'No snippet')

print(f"\nResult {j}:")
print(f"Title: {title}")
print(f"Snippet: {snippet}")
print(f"Link: {link}")

# Check for key gang-related terms
combined_text = f"{title.lower()} {snippet.lower()}"
gang_terms = ['pierpont', 'dillinger', 'hudson', 'bank robbery', 'indiana', '1924', '1934', 'gang', 'heist']

matching_terms = [term for term in gang_terms if term in combined_text]
if matching_terms:
print(f"ðŸŽ¯ RELEVANT - Contains: {', '.join(matching_terms)}")

# Store result
all_focused_results.append({
'query_number': i,
'query_text': query,
'result_number': j,
'title': title,
'link': link,
'snippet': snippet,
'matching_terms': matching_terms
})

print("-" * 40)
else:
print(f"No results found for query: '{query}'")

else:
print(f"API request failed with status {response.status_code}")
if response.text:
print(f"Error details: {response.text[:200]}...")

except requests.exceptions.Timeout:
print(f"Timeout occurred for query {i}. Moving to next query.")
except Exception as e:
print(f"Error during search {i}: {str(e)}")

print("\n" + "="*80)

# Save focused search results
focused_results_file = 'workspace/focused_gang_search_results.json'
with open(focused_results_file, 'w', encoding='utf-8') as f:
json.dump({
'search_timestamp': datetime.now().isoformat(),
'search_type': 'focused_gang_search',
'search_purpose': 'Identify Pierpont-Bridgewater-Northern gang with improved timeout handling',
'total_queries': len(focused_queries),
'total_results': len(all_focused_results),
'queries': focused_queries,
'results': all_focused_results
}, f, indent=2, ensure_ascii=False)

print(f"\n\nðŸ“Š FOCUSED SEARCH SUMMARY:")

import os import requests from bs4 import BeautifulSoup import json from datetime import datetime import time # Since the SerpAPI quota is exhausted, let's try alternative approaches # First, let's check what files we have in workspace from previous searches print("Checking workspace for existing research files...") print("=" * 60) workspace_files = [] if os.path.exists('workspace'): for file in os.listdir('workspace'): if file.endswith('.json') or file.endswith('.txt'): workspace_files.append(file) print(f"Found file: {file}") print(f"\nTotal files found: {len(workspace_files)}") # Let's inspect any existing search results that might contain relevant information for file in workspace_files: if 'dillinger' in file.lower() or 'gang' in file.lower() or 'pierpont' in file.lower(): print(f"\nðŸ“ Inspecting potentially relevant file: {file}") file_path = f'workspace/{file}' try: if file.endswith('.json'): with open(file_path, 'r', encoding='utf-8') as f: data = json.load(f) print(f"JSON file structure: {list(data.keys())[:5]}...") # Show first 5 keys # Look for any mentions of physical descriptions or execution details if 'all_search_results' in data: results = data['all_search_results'] print(f"Contains {len(results)} search results") # Search through existing results for physical descriptions physical_mentions = [] execution_mentions = [] for result in results: if isinstance(result, dict) and 'snippet' in result: snippet = result.get('snippet', '').lower() title = result.get('title', '').lower() combined = f"{title} {snippet}" # Look for physical descriptions physical_terms = ['feet', 'webbed', 'syndactyly', 'deformity', 'physical', 'abnormal', 'disability'] if any(term in combined for term in physical_terms): physical_mentions.append(result) print(f"ðŸ¦¶ Physical description found: {result.get('title', '')[:50]}...") # Look for execution details execution_terms = ['execution', 'executed', 'electric chair', 'death penalty', 'prison'] if any(term in combined for term in execution_terms): execution_mentions.append(result) print(f"Physical description mentions: {len(physical_mentions)}") print(f"Execution mentions: {len(execution_mentions)}") elif file.endswith('.txt'): with open(file_path, 'r', encoding='utf-8') as f: content = f.read() print(f"Text file length: {len(content)} characters") # Search for physical abnormality mentions in text files content_lower = content.lower() if any(term in content_lower for term in ['webbed', 'syndactyly', 'feet', 'physical']): print("ðŸ¦¶ Physical abnormality references found in text file!") # Extract relevant sections lines = content.split('\n') relevant_lines = [] for line in lines: if any(term in line.lower() for term in ['webbed', 'syndactyly', 'feet', 'physical', 'deformity']): relevant_lines.append(line.strip()) if relevant_lines: print("Relevant excerpts:") for line in relevant_lines[:3]: # Show first 3 relevant lines print(f" - {line}") except Exception as e: print(f"Error reading file {file}: {e}") print("-" * 40) # Now let's try direct web scraping for historical execution records print("\n\nðŸ” ATTEMPTING DIRECT WEB SCRAPING FOR EXECUTION RECORDS") print("=" * 60) # Try to access historical databases and archives directly target_urls = [ 'https://www.findagrave.com', # Often has execution details 'https://deathpenaltyinfo.org', # Death penalty database 'https://murderpedia.org' # Crime database ] headers = { 'User-Agent': 'Mozilla/5.0 (Windows NT 10.0; Win64; x64) AppleWebKit/537.36 (KHTML, like Gecko) Chrome/91.0.4472.124 Safari/537.36' } # Search for specific information about Harry Pierpont, Charles Makley, and Russell Clark search_terms = { 'Harry Pierpont': ['execution', 'electric chair', 'Indiana State Prison', 'webbed feet', 'physical abnormality'], 'Charles Makley': ['execution', 'killed', 'escape attempt', 'Indiana State Prison', 'physical description'], 'Russell Clark': ['execution', 'death sentence', 'commuted', 'Indiana State Prison', 'physical features'] } print("Searching for historical execution records...") print("Target individuals: Harry Pierpont, Charles Makley, Russell Clark") print("Focus: Physical abnormalities, execution details, prison records") # Create a comprehensive research summary based on known historical facts historical_summary = """ ðŸŽ¯ HISTORICAL EXECUTION RECORDS RESEARCH SUMMARY =============================================== Target: Identify individual with webbed feet/syndactyly among 1930s Indiana executions KNOWN HISTORICAL FACTS: 1. HARRY PIERPONT: - Executed: October 17, 1934 - Location: Indiana State Prison, Michigan City - Method: Electric chair - Crime: Murder of Sheriff Jess Sarber during Lima, Ohio jailbreak - Gang role: Leader of Pierpont-Bridgewater-Northern gang - Physical description: [RESEARCH TARGET - webbed feet?] 2. import os import json from datetime import datetime # Following the tester's feedback, let's thoroughly analyze the existing 17 workspace files # First, let's inspect each file's structure before extracting content print("ðŸ” COMPREHENSIVE ANALYSIS OF EXISTING WORKSPACE FILES") print("Target: Find mentions of webbed feet, syndactyly, or physical descriptions") print("Focus: Harry Pierpont, Charles Makley, Russell Clark") print("=" * 80) workspace_files = [] if os.path.exists('workspace'): for file in os.listdir('workspace'): if file.endswith('.json') or file.endswith('.txt'): workspace_files.append(file) print(f"Found {len(workspace_files)} files to analyze\n") # Track all findings related to physical descriptions physical_findings = [] gang_member_mentions = { 'pierpont': [], 'makley': [], 'clark': [] } # Analyze each file systematically for i, filename in enumerate(workspace_files, 1): print(f"ðŸ“ File {i}/{len(workspace_files)}: {filename}") print("-" * 60) file_path = f'workspace/{filename}' try: if filename.endswith('.json'): # First inspect JSON structure with open(file_path, 'r', encoding='utf-8') as f: data = json.load(f) print(f"JSON structure - Keys: {list(data.keys())[:10]}...") # Show first 10 keys print(f"Data type: {type(data)}") # Look for search results or content arrays content_fields = ['all_search_results', 'results', 'search_results', 'content', 'findings'] for field in content_fields: if field in data: print(f"Found content field: {field}") content = data[field] if isinstance(content, list): print(f"Contains {len(content)} items") # Search through each item for physical descriptions for item_idx, item in enumerate(content): if isinstance(item, dict): # Check all text fields in the item text_fields = ['title', 'snippet', 'description', 'content', 'text'] for text_field in text_fields: if text_field in item and isinstance(item[text_field], str): text_content = item[text_field].lower() # Search for physical abnormality terms physical_terms = ['webbed', 'syndactyly', 'feet', 'foot', 'toes', 'deformity', 'abnormality', 'physical defect', 'birth defect'] for term in physical_terms: if term in text_content: finding = { 'file': filename, 'item_index': item_idx, 'field': text_field, 'term_found': term, 'content': item[text_field][:200] + '...' if len(item[text_field]) > 200 else item[text_field], 'full_item': item } physical_findings.append(finding) print(f"ðŸ¦¶ PHYSICAL TERM FOUND: '{term}' in {text_field}") print(f" Content preview: {item[text_field][:100]}...") # Search for gang member names if 'pierpont' in text_content: gang_member_mentions['pierpont'].append({ 'file': filename, 'content': item[text_field][:200] + '...' if len(item[text_field]) > 200 else item[text_field] }) print(f"ðŸ‘¤ PIERPONT MENTION in {text_field}") if 'makley' in text_content: gang_member_mentions['makley'].append({ 'file': filename, 'content': item[text_field][:200] + '...' if len(item[text_field]) > 200 else item[text_field] }) print(f"ðŸ‘¤ MAKLEY MENTION in {text_field}") if 'clark' in text_content and 'russell' in text_content: gang_member_mentions['clark'].append({ 'file': filename, 'content': item[text_field][:200] + '...' if len(item[text_field]) > 200 else item[text_field] }) print(f"ðŸ‘¤ RUSSELL CLARK MENTION in {text_field}") elif isinstance(content, str): # Direct string content content_lower = content.lower() # Search for physical terms physical_terms = ['webbed', 'syndactyly', 'feet', 'foot', 'toes', 'deformity', 'abnormality'] for term in physical_terms: if term in content_lower: finding = { 'file': filename, 'field': field, 'term_found': term, 'content': content[:300] + '...' if len(content) > 300 else content } physical_findings.append(finding) print(f"ðŸ¦¶ PHYSICAL TERM FOUND: '{term}' in string content") # Also check top-level string fields for key, value in data.items(): if isinstance(value, str) and len(value) > 10: value_lower = value.lower() physical_terms = ['webbed', 'syndactyly', 'feet', 'foot', 'toes', 'deformity', 'abnormality'] for term in physical_terms: if term in value_lower: finding = { 'file': filename, 'field': key, 'term_found': term, 'content': value[:300] + '...' if len(value) > 300 else value } physical_findings.append(finding) print(f"ðŸ¦¶ PHYSICAL TERM FOUND: '{term}' in {key}") elif filename.endswith('.txt'): # Analyze text files with open(file_path, 'r', encoding='utf-8') as f: content = f.read() print(f"Text file length: {len(content)} characters") content_lower = content.lower() # Search for physical abnormality terms physical_terms = ['webbed', 'syndactyly', 'feet', 'foot', 'toes', 'deformity', 'abnormality', 'physical defect'] for term in physical_terms: if term in content_lower: # Find the context around the term term_index = content_lower.find(term) start_idx = max(0, term_index - 100) end_idx = min(len(content), term_index + 100) context = content[start_idx:end_idx] finding = { 'file': filename, 'term_found': term, 'context': context, 'full_content': content } physical_findings.append(finding) print(f"ðŸ¦¶ PHYSICAL TERM FOUND: '{term}'") print(f" Context: ...{context}...") # Search for gang member names with physical descriptions lines = content.split('\n') for line_num, line in enumerate(lines): line_lower = line.lower() # Look for lines mentioning gang members AND physical terms if any(name in line_lower for name in ['pierpont', 'makley', 'clark']): if any(term in line_lower for term in physical_terms): print(f"ðŸŽ¯ GANG MEMBER + PHYSICAL TERM in line {line_num}: {line.strip()}") finding = { 'file': filename, 'line_number': line_num, 'content': line.strip(), 'type': 'gang_member_physical_description' } physical_findings.append(finding) except Exception as e: print(f"Error analyzing file {filename}: {e}") print("\n" + "=" * 80 + "\n") # Summarize findings print("\n\nðŸ“Š COMPREHENSIVE ANALYSIS RESULTS") print("=" * 50) print(f"\nðŸ¦¶ PHYSICAL ABNORMALITY FINDINGS: {len(physical_findings)}") if physical_findings: print("\nDetailed findings:") for i, finding in enumerate(physical_findings, 1): print(f"\n{i}. File: {finding['file']}") print(f" Term found: {finding['term_found']}") if 'context' in finding: print(f" Context: {finding['context']}") elif 'content' in finding: print(f" Content: {finding['content']}") # Check if this finding mentions any gang members content_to_check = finding.get('content', finding.get('context', '')) if content_to_check: content_lower = content_to_check.lower() if 'pierpont' in content_lower: print(f" â­ MENTIONS HARRY PIERPONT!") if 'makley' in content_lower: print(f" â­ MENTIONS CHARLES MAKLEY!") if 'clark' in content_lower: print(f" â­ MENTIONS RUSSELL CLARK!") else: print("No physical abnormality terms found in existing files.") print(f"\nðŸ‘¤ GANG MEMBER MENTIONS:") print(f"Harry Pierpont: {len(gang_member_mentions['pierpont'])} mentions") print(f"Charles Makley: {len(gang_member_mentions['makley'])} mentions") print(f"Russell Clark: {len(gang_member_mentions['clark'])} mentions") # Save comprehensive analysis results analysis_results = { 'analysis_timestamp': datetime.now().isoformat(), 'files_analyzed': len(workspace_files), 'physical_findings_count': len(physical_findings), 'physical_findings': physical_findings, 'gang_member_mentions': gang_member_mentions, 'search_target': 'webbed feet/syndactyly among Harry Pierpont, Charles Makley, Russell Clark' } results_file = 'workspace/comprehensive_file_analysis_results.json' with open(results_file, 'w', encoding='utf-8') as f: json.dump(analysis_results, f, indent=2, ensure_ascii=False) print(f"\nðŸ“„ Comprehensive analysis results saved to: {results_file}") # import os import json from datetime import datetime # Following the tester's feedback, let's thoroughly analyze the existing 17 workspace files # First, let's inspect each file's structure before extracting content print("ðŸ” COMPREHENSIVE ANALYSIS OF EXISTING WORKSPACE FILES") print("Target: Find mentions of webbed feet, syndactyly, or physical descriptions") print("Focus: Harry Pierpont, Charles Makley, Russell Clark") print("=" * 80) workspace_files = [] if os.path.exists('workspace'): for file in os.listdir('workspace'): if file.endswith('.json') or file.endswith('.txt'): workspace_files.append(file) print(f"Found {len(workspace_files)} files to analyze\n") # Look for search results or content arrays content_fields = ['all_search_results', 'results', 'search_results', 'content', 'findings'] for field in content_fields: if field in data: print(f"Found content field: {field}") content = data[field] if isinstance(content, list): print(f"Contains {len(content)} items") # Search through each item for physical descriptions for item_idx, item in enumerate(content): if isinstance(item, dict): # Check all text fields in the item text_fields = ['title', 'snippet', 'description', 'content', 'text'] for text_field in text_fields: if text_field in item and isinstance(item[text_field], str): text_content = item[text_field].lower() # Search for physical abnormality terms physical_terms = ['webbed', 'syndactyly', 'feet', 'foot', 'toes', 'deformity', 'abnormality', 'physical defect', 'birth defect'] for term in physical_terms: if term in text_content: finding = { 'file': filename, 'item_index': item_idx, 'field': text_field, 'term_found': term, 'content': item[text_field][:200] + '...' if len(item[text_field]) > 200 else item[text_field], 'full_item': item } physical_findings.append(finding) print(f"ðŸ¦¶ PHYSICAL TERM FOUND: '{term}' in {text_field}") print(f" Content preview: {item[text_field][:100]}...") # Search for gang member names if 'pierpont' in text_content: gang_member_mentions['pierpont'].append({ 'file': filename, 'content': item[text_field][:200] + '...' if len(item[text_field]) > 200 else item[text_field] }) print(f"ðŸ‘¤ PIERPONT MENTION in {text_field}") if 'makley' in text_content: gang_member_mentions['makley'].append({ 'file': filename, 'content': item[text_field][:200] + '...' if len(item[text_field]) > 200 else item[text_field] }) print(f"ðŸ‘¤ MAKLEY MENTION in {text_field}") if 'clark' in text_content and 'russell' in text_content: gang_member_mentions['clark'].append({ 'file': filename, 'content': item[text_field][:200] + '...' if len(item[text_field]) > 200 else item[text_field] }) print(f"ðŸ‘¤ RUSSELL CLARK MENTION in {text_field}") elif isinstance(content, str): # Direct string content content_lower = content.lower() # Search for physical terms physical_terms = ['webbed', 'syndactyly', 'feet', 'foot', 'toes', 'deformity', 'abnormality'] for term in physical_terms: if term in content_lower: finding = { 'file': filename, 'field': field, 'term_found': term, 'content': content[:300] + '...' if len(content) > 300 else content } physical_findings.append(finding) print(f"ðŸ¦¶ PHYSICAL TERM FOUND: '{term}' in string content") # Also check top-level string fields for key, value in data.items(): if isinstance(value, str) and len(value) > 10: value_lower = value.lower() physical_terms = ['webbed', 'syndactyly', 'feet', 'foot', 'toes', 'deformity', 'abnormality'] for term in physical_terms: if term in value_lower: finding = { 'file': filename, 'field': key, 'term_found': term, 'content': value[:300] + '...' if len(value) > 300 else value } physical_findings.append(finding) print(f"ðŸ¦¶ PHYSICAL TERM FOUND: '{term}' in {key}") elif filename.endswith('.txt'): # Analyze text files with open(file_path, 'r', encoding='utf-8') as f: content = f.read() print(f"Text file length: {len(content)} characters") content_lower = content.lower() # Search for physical abnormality terms physical_terms = ['webbed', 'syndactyly', 'feet', 'foot', 'toes', 'deformity', 'abnormality', 'physical defect'] for term in physical_terms: if term in content_lower: # Find the context around the term term_index = content_lower.find(term) start_idx = max(0, term_index - 100) end_idx = min(len(content), term_index + 100) context = content[start_idx:end_idx] finding = { 'file': filename, 'term_found': term, 'context': context, 'full_content': content } physical_findings.append(finding) print(f"ðŸ¦¶ PHYSICAL TERM FOUND: '{term}'") print(f" Context: ...{context}...") # Search for gang member names with physical descriptions lines = content.split('\n') for line_num, line in enumerate(lines): line_lower = line.lower() # Look for lines mentioning gang members AND physical terms if any(name in line_lower for name in ['pierpont', 'makley', 'clark']): if any(term in line_lower for term in physical_terms): print(f"ðŸŽ¯ GANG MEMBER + PHYSICAL TERM in line {line_num}: {line.strip()}") finding = { 'file': filename, 'line_number': line_num, 'content': line.strip(), 'type': 'gang_member_physical_description' } physical_findings.append(finding) except Exception as e: print(f"Error analyzing file {filename}: {e}") print("\n" + "=" * 80 + "\n") #
